The paper focuses on studying the browsing behavior of online users, which is a topic related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social networks (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of search engines (cs.IR) and online advertisement (cs.CY), which are related to information retrieval and cybersecurity, respectively. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of a browser add-on to track user behavior, which could fall under the category of computer networks and communications (cs.CR).
